# Constants Module Naming

In constants modules, name the top-level returned constants table using uppercase snake case.

Use the uppercase table name to signal immutable configuration intent.
Also name exported constant keys using uppercase snake case (for example `PROVIDER_TAG`).
When requiring constants modules in other files, bind them to uppercase snake case locals too (for example `local TOOL_PROVIDER = require(...)`).

## Prefer

```luau
local TOOL_PROVIDER: ToolProviderConstants = {
	PROVIDER_TAG = "ToolProvider",
	POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS = 0.25,
}

return TOOL_PROVIDER
```

## Avoid

```luau
local ToolProvider: ToolProviderConstants = {
	providerTag = "ToolProvider",
	pollIntervalSeconds = 0.25,
}

return ToolProvider
```
